<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1182,2034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,1182,1207]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Forewing length of male 
<quantity box="[561,714,1182,1206]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.75" metricValueMax="3.89" metricValueMin="3.61" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="3.75" valueMax="3.89" valueMin="3.61">3.61–3.89 cm</quantity>
(mean = 
<number box="[820,872,1182,1206]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="3.77">3.77</number>
, n = 
<number box="[925,940,1182,1206]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="5.0">5</number>
), and female 
<quantity box="[1092,1245,1182,1206]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.205" metricValueMax="4.32" metricValueMin="4.09" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" unit="cm" value="4.205" valueMax="4.32" valueMin="4.09">4.09–4.32 cm</quantity>
(mean = 
<number box="[1351,1389,1182,1206]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="4.2">4.2</number>
, n = 
<number box="[151,167,1218,1242]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="3.0">3</number>
). Dorsal forewing basal to medial areas pale yellow, notably lighter in color than 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1081,1174,1219,1243]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis box="[1081,1174,1219,1243]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1229,1381,1219,1243]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis box="[1229,1381,1219,1243]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and usually outlined distally by an orange tinge. Ventral forewing brown postmedial band often thinner than those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[269,422,1291,1315]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis box="[269,422,1291,1315]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; this band is thicker from M 
<number box="[753,763,1290,1314]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
to the middle of the Cu 
<number box="[1039,1048,1290,1314]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
cell, becoming thinner and with a zigzag pattern from there to 
<number box="[478,487,1326,1350]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
A+ 
<number box="[526,540,1326,1350]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.0">2</number>
A (the zigzag pattern corresponds to the edge of the yellow area on the dorsal surface). Dorsal hind wing yellow area pale such that the underside pattern is visible dorsally, brown band form the postmedial to marginal area narrower than in 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[659,751,1398,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis box="[659,751,1398,1423]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[805,957,1398,1423]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis box="[805,957,1398,1423]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, usually interspersed by pale yellow spots. Females similar to males except for the better defined dorsal marginal and submarginal pale yellow spots on both wings.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1182,2034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,314,1506,1531]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Given the smaller size of this species, both the male and female genitalia are proportionately smaller than those of 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[390,483,1542,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis box="[390,483,1542,1567]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[536,689,1542,1567]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis box="[536,689,1542,1567]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Male specimens (three dissections, two without locality data) varied in the width of the distal half of the valva, and also the number of subterminal spines at the dorsal edge (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1722]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,198,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1388,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Blepolenis male and female genitalia, including dissection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. Male genitalia is illustrated in lateral and ventral views (setae omitted from right side of figure to emphasize the shape), an outline of the tegumen is given in dorsal view, and outlines of the distal portion of the valva in lateral view show the variation in the dorsal, subterminal spines. The ventral view of female sterigma includes most, but not all the length of the lateral arms. All drawings in the same scale except for corpus bursa; scale bars 1 mm, appearing under A and C. A, Blepolenis bassus male, Murtinho, Paraná, 09 - 14. B, B. bassus male valvae, top figure is the left valva of the specimen in A; bottom left, Brazil, 01 - 31; bottom right, Brazil, 08 - 41. C, B. bassus female (the irregular signa are an artifact of preparation), São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. D, B. batea male, Serra do Caraça, Minas Gerais, 09 - 05. E, B. batea male valvae, top to bottom, left to right: Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33; S. Paulo, 09 - 04; Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15; Nova Teutônia, Santa Catarina, 08 - 42. F, B. batea female, Santa Catarina, 06 - 16. G, B. catharinae male, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 01. H, no data, 09 - 15. I, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 02." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205028/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,165,1614,1638]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
A, B). Female sterigma with long lateral arms, and a longer and narrower midline lobe than those in 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1295,1389,1614,1639]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis box="[1295,1389,1614,1639]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[151,303,1651,1675]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="catharinae">
<emphasis box="[151,303,1651,1675]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. catharinae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(but only one female was dissected). Corpus bursa oval shaped, with paired signa, and constricted at the meeting point with the narrow ductus bursa (
<figureCitation box="[694,762,1686,1710]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1699,1722]" captionTargetBox="[202,1383,198,1674]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[194,1388,193,1678]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Blepolenis male and female genitalia, including dissection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. Male genitalia is illustrated in lateral and ventral views (setae omitted from right side of figure to emphasize the shape), an outline of the tegumen is given in dorsal view, and outlines of the distal portion of the valva in lateral view show the variation in the dorsal, subterminal spines. The ventral view of female sterigma includes most, but not all the length of the lateral arms. All drawings in the same scale except for corpus bursa; scale bars 1 mm, appearing under A and C. A, Blepolenis bassus male, Murtinho, Paraná, 09 - 14. B, B. bassus male valvae, top figure is the left valva of the specimen in A; bottom left, Brazil, 01 - 31; bottom right, Brazil, 08 - 41. C, B. bassus female (the irregular signa are an artifact of preparation), São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. D, B. batea male, Serra do Caraça, Minas Gerais, 09 - 05. E, B. batea male valvae, top to bottom, left to right: Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33; S. Paulo, 09 - 04; Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15; Nova Teutônia, Santa Catarina, 08 - 42. F, B. batea female, Santa Catarina, 06 - 16. G, B. catharinae male, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 01. H, no data, 09 - 15. I, Lagoa do Peri, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina, 09 - 02." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205028/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[747,762,1686,1710]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2.0">2</number>
</figureCitation>
C).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[197,979,1722,1747]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1182,2034]" box="[197,979,1722,1747]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,350,1722,1747]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[357,428,1722,1746]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, Atlantic forest, São Paulo to Rio Grande do Sul.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,1182,2034]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,499,1758,1783]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Variation and subspecies.</emphasis>
Some variation in wing color has been identified, such as the size of the pale yellow spots at the dorsal hind wing margin (see males in 
<figureCitation box="[713,774,1794,1818]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[764,774,1794,1818]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
A and D, and females in 
<figureCitation box="[1054,1116,1794,1818]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1105,1116,1794,1818]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B and C). As noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fruhstorfer" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" refString="Fruhstorfer, H. (1912) 5. Familie: Brassolidae. p. 285 - 328. In: Seitz, A. (ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Stuttgart, volume 5. Alfred Kernen." type="book chapter" year="1912">
Fruhstorfer (
<number box="[242,300,1830,1854]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1912.0">1912</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
the association of wing color with subspecific forms seems arbitrary. This probably led to Casagrande’s (
<number box="[267,326,1866,1890]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2004.0">2004</number>
) proposal that 
<taxonomicName authority="Butler, 1874" authorityName="Butler" authorityYear="1874" box="[514,927,1866,1891]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="bassus" subSpecies="luteipenis">
<emphasis box="[514,749,1867,1891]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. bassus luteipenis</emphasis>
(Butler, 
<number box="[862,920,1866,1890]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1874.0">1874</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
be considered a synonym of the nominal subspecies. We note that two females from Campos do Jordão, São Paulo state (
<figureCitation box="[1094,1161,1902,1926]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[1150,1161,1902,1926]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
C), appear to be darker orange in color, and with larger pale yellow spots at the dorsal hind wing margin than those from more southern localities (
<figureCitation box="[268,332,1974,1998]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1724,1747]" captionTargetBox="[152,1428,381,1693]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,375,1700]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Adult Blepolenis butterflies of both sexes in dorsal (D) and ventral (V) views, including dissection or collection numbers as listed in Appendix 1. A, Blepolenis bassus male D &amp; V, Brazil, 08 - 41. B, B. bassus female D &amp; V, São Bento [do Sul], [Rio Grande do Sul], 01 - 32. C, B. bassus female D, Campos do Jordão-Lagoinha, [São Paulo] MZSP 13714. D, B. bassus male D, Murtinho, E. Parana, MZSP 13711. E, B. batea male D &amp; V, Santa Catarina, 08 - 38. F, B. batea female D &amp; V, Santa Catarina. G, B. batea male D &amp; V, Itatiba, São Paulo, MZSP 13719. H, B. batea male D, Pelotas, Rio Grande do Sul, 06 - 15. I, B. batea male D, Porto Alegre, MZSP 13709. J, B. batea male D, S. Paulo, 09 - 04, MZSP 13718. K, B. batea male D, Nova Friburgo, Rio de Janeiro, 01 - 33. L, B. catharinae male D, no locality, specimen from the Fruhstorfer Collection, B. M. [N. H.] 1937 - 285. M, B. catharinae male D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. N, B. catharinae female D &amp; V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina. O, B. catharinae male D, no locality, 09 - 15, MZSP 13710. P, B. catharinae male V, Florianópolis, Santa Catarina." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/205027/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
Fig. 
<number box="[321,332,1974,1998]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1.0">1</number>
</figureCitation>
B). Mirna Casagrande (pers. comm.) notes that females of 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1000,1107,1974,1999]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bassus">
<emphasis box="[1000,1107,1974,1999]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">B. bassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
may vary in color within the same population.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,151,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,458,151,176]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Natural history notes.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Fruhstorfer" box="[466,674,151,175]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" refString="Fruhstorfer, H. (1912) 5. Familie: Brassolidae. p. 285 - 328. In: Seitz, A. (ed.), Die Gross-Schmetterlinge der Erde. Stuttgart, volume 5. Alfred Kernen." type="book chapter" year="1912">
Fruhstorfer (
<number box="[607,665,151,175]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1912.0">1912</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
indicated that 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[841,947,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bassus">
<emphasis box="[841,947,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. bassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is commonly found with 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[1238,1331,152,176]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="batea">
<emphasis box="[1238,1331,152,176]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. batea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and that unlike the latter, 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[347,455,188,212]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bassus">
<emphasis box="[347,455,188,212]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. bassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
“ventures even in the greatest heat of the day on to sunny grass-lands with scattered bushes.” Andre Freitas (pers. comm.) observed 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[702,812,224,248]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bassus">
<emphasis box="[702,812,224,248]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. bassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ovipositing on grass in Capão Bonito (Fazenda Intervales), São Paulo state, but the early stages of 
<taxonomicName authority="Julius Röber, 1906" authorityName="Julius Röber" authorityYear="1906" box="[669,775,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Blepolenis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bassus">
<emphasis box="[669,775,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. bassus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
remain unknown.
</paragraph>
